Webinar Speakers

Stephen Flynn

Senior Credit Analyst·Bloomberg Intelligence

Stephen Flynn is a senior credit analyst for Bloomberg Intelligence, a unique research platform that provides context on industries, companies, litigation, government policy and the economy, available on the Bloomberg Professional service at BI <GO>. Mr. Flynn specializes in the media, cable and telecommunications services sectors.   Mr. Flynn joined Bloomberg in 2015 and has over 15 years of leveraged and investment grade corporate credit research experience. Prior to joining Bloomberg, he was a Managing Director at Morgan Stanley, where he worked as a senior high yield analyst and the head of Morgan Stanley’s corporate credit desk analyst effort.  Stephen has an MBA from The Leonard N. Stern School of Business at New York University and an undergraduate degree from Lehigh University. 

Neil Mack

VP, Senior Analyst·Moody's

Neil Mack is a Vice President - Senior Analyst on Moody’s Telecommunications/Media Team covering a portfolio of investment grade and high yield telecommunications companies. Prior to joining Moody’s in 2017 he held various positions in fixed income asset management, including at Citigroup Asset Management, Bear Stearns, AllianceBernstein and PartnerRe Asset Management. Neil is a CFA charterholder and a member of the New York Society of Security Analysts. He received his MBA in Finance from Columbia University and BA in English from Fordham University.

Emile El Nems

VP, Senior Credit Officer·Moody's

Emile El Nems is a Vice President - Senior Credit Officer on the Technology, Media and Telecommunications Team covering a portfolio of investment grade and high yield issuers in a number of verticals, including social media, diversified telecommunication service providers, media, entertainment and interactive media services. Prior to his work on the Technology, Media and Telecommunications Team, Emile covered issuers on the Homebuilding, Building Materials and Packaging Team. Prior to joining Moody’s in 2019 as a VP-Lead Analyst, Emile was a portfolio manager at a large US hedge fund for five years and a managing director responsible for a Technology, Media and Telecommunications portfolio at a European hedge fund for seven years. Before his asset management experience, Emile was a principal in the Investment Banking Group at Thomas Weisel Partners and a team leader in the Investment Banking Group at Banc of America Securities covering global wireline and wireless telecommunications, cable, and media companies. Emile received his MBA in finance from Columbia University and BS in Chemical Engineering from Stevens

Jason Cuomo

Senior Vice President·Moody's

Jason Cuomo is a Senior Vice President in the Corporate Finance Group. He is the lead rating analyst for a diversified portfolio of high-yield and investment grade cable, telecommunication, and media credits that hold more than $120 billion in debt. He is a voting member of rating committees, and a rating chair. Mr. Cuomo joined the firm in 2006. Mr. Cuomo is a thought leader on individual credits, sector outlooks, financial adequacy, emerging credit trends and accounting topics supported by at least 300 publications. His work has influenced capital market flows, investment decisions, global changes in analytic methodologies, credit policy, and US GAAP. He is also active in corporate projects to develop technology solutions that automate the firm’s analytic tools and processes, as Co-head of the Americas initiative to identify and adopt enabling technologies.

Sean Cray

Analyst·Moody's

Sean Cray is a lead analyst on the Business and Consumer Services team within the US Corporate Finance Group. Sean covers a portfolio of services and software companies across various verticals including consulting, business process outsourcers, deathcare and others. Prior to joining the Services team in 2020, Sean covered investment grade and speculative grade issuers throughout the telecom, media, consumer products and gaming industries. Prior to joining Moody's in 2008, Sean worked as a financial analyst at AIG. Sean holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Finance from Rutgers University.

Description

Wednesday, May 21, 2025 at 10:30-11:30am ET ** Call is not open to the media. There will be no recording/replay nor transcript available following the call. Please make sure to mark in your calendars as individual calendar invite will not be sent.** Note: Call is not open to media. Featured Speaker Farrukh Bezar, Chairman, STS Logistics (Private) Hosted by Jason Seidl, Rail, Trucking & Logistics Senior Analyst Discussion Topics • Current IM trends, pull forward impacts, tariff implications. • Path to rail conversion and service quality offering. • Outlook for rail and IM pricing. • Regulatory environment, new policy implications. About Farrukh Bezar Mr. Bezar brings more than 25 years of transportation and logistics industry expertise as a strategist and analyst. He served as a Senior Vice President and Chief Strategy Officer at CSX Corporation until 2024, responsible for leading the company’s strategic growth initiatives. Prior to joining CSX in May 2019, Mr. Bezar founded and led Lynwood Partners, a transportation and logistics advisory firm. His previous experience includes senior leadership roles within the transportation and logistics functions at Clarendon, Booz Allen Hamilton, and A.T. Kearney. He also previously held sales and marketing positions at the CSX, Atchison, Topeka, and Santa Fe Railway Company and served as a financial analyst with Chase Manhattan Bank. Mr. Bezar holds an MBA from the J.L. Kellogg Graduate School of Management at Northwestern University and a BA also from Northwestern. He currently serves on the boards of Littlejohn portfolio company, Magnate Worldwide, as well as STG as Chairman and the Northwestern Transportation Advisory Board. *Please submit questions via email to Jason.Seidl@tdsecurities.com Note: There will be no replay or transcript available for this call.
